BIB                 15         30
TITLE      Production of no-carrier added 67Cu
AUTHOR     (S.Mirzadeh,L.F.Mausner,S.C.Srivastava)
REFERENCE  (J,ARI,37,29,1986)
           #doi:10.1016/0883-2889(86)90192-9
REL-REF    (O,C3102001,S.Mirzadeh+,J,ARI,37,29,1986) Proton data.
INSTITUTE  (1USABNL)
FACILITY   (REAC,1USABNL) BNL-HIgh Flux Beam Reactor, HFBR.
INC-SOURCE (REAC)
DETECTOR   (GELI) 50 cc detector.
SAMPLE     (30-ZN-67,ENR=0.932) The Zn target as 67ZnO (with
           enrichment of 93.2%, obtained from ORNL) encapsulated
           in a quartz tube.
METHOD     (ACTIV) Copper-67 was produced by irradiation of 67Zn
           in a nuclear reactor, in-core and core-edge, of the
           BNL High Flux Beam Reactor for periods ranging from a
           few hours to several days. Activities were measured
           with a calibrated Ge gamma-ray detector connected to
           a 4096 channel analyzer.
